1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,883
This phone is training a Transformer locally.

2
00:00:01,883 --> 00:00:02,690
No cloud service.

3
00:00:02,690 --> 00:00:03,767
No mobile-only inference runtime.

4
00:00:03,767 --> 00:00:06,457
The same OA operation library, autograd engine, AdamW optimizer,

5
00:00:06,457 --> 00:00:09,417
checkpoint format, and Vulkan kernels also run on an Intel desktop.

6
00:00:09,417 --> 00:00:11,838
The same capability-driven runtime has NVIDIA, AMD, Intel, and

7
00:00:11,838 --> 00:00:13,990
Qualcomm paths across discrete, integrated, and mobile GPUs.

8
00:00:13,990 --> 00:00:15,605
The phone is not the product.

9
00:00:15,605 --> 00:00:17,488
It is proof that the architecture travels.

10
00:00:17,868 --> 00:00:20,865
GPU software is usually assembled from separate stacks for numerical

11
00:00:20,865 --> 00:00:23,262
compute, machine learning, vision, audio, codecs, and presentation.

12
00:00:23,262 --> 00:00:25,659
Each boundary introduces another data model, allocator, copy,

13
00:00:25,659 --> 00:00:27,157
synchronization rule, and hardware backend.

14
00:00:27,157 --> 00:00:30,154
Python makes the surface approachable, but crossing layers can still

15
00:00:30,154 --> 00:00:31,352
fragment the work underneath.

16
00:00:31,352 --> 00:00:34,049
The result is familiar: powerful accelerators, surrounded by glue.

17
00:00:34,429 --> 00:00:38,063
OA tests a different idea: one GPU-first C++ and Python

18
00:00:38,063 --> 00:00:38,971
framework over Vulkan.

19
00:00:38,971 --> 00:00:41,696
Matrices, images, audio buffers, and video frames keep their

20
00:00:41,696 --> 00:00:44,421
meaning, while one engine owns device memory, kernel selection,

21
00:00:44,421 --> 00:00:45,935
graph execution, scheduling, and profiling.

22
00:00:45,935 --> 00:00:46,844
Operations stay stateless.

23
00:00:46,844 --> 00:00:47,752
Sessions own state.

24
00:00:47,752 --> 00:00:50,174
Semantic work lowers into dispatches, transfers, barriers, resource

25
00:00:50,174 --> 00:00:51,385
aliases, and explicit completion.

26
00:00:51,385 --> 00:00:54,111
Capabilities are selected at runtime, and unsupported paths fail

27
00:00:54,111 --> 00:00:54,413
visibly.

28
00:00:54,793 --> 00:00:56,989
For Build Week, we made that claim physical.

29
00:00:56,989 --> 00:01:00,009
OA Mobile Lab trains five small neural network architectures on an

30
00:01:00,009 --> 00:01:03,303
Adreno phone: an RNN, a GRU, a Transformer,

31
00:01:03,303 --> 00:01:05,225
a sparse mixture-of-experts Transformer, and Mamba-3.

32
00:01:05,225 --> 00:01:07,970
A route passes only after forward, loss, backward, AdamW,

33
00:01:07,970 --> 00:01:09,617
evaluation, autoregressive generation, checkpoint save, fresh-model

34
00:01:09,617 --> 00:01:10,990
reload, and exact generation parity.

35
00:01:10,990 --> 00:01:12,912
The controlled Transformer and mixture-of-experts contracts also

36
00:01:12,912 --> 00:01:14,559
pass on Intel Iris Xe.

37
00:01:14,939 --> 00:01:17,581
That result is difficult because training is not one kernel.

38
00:01:17,581 --> 00:01:19,960
It is thousands of coupled decisions about shapes, lifetimes,

39
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:21,810
precision, descriptors, memory visibility, and device capabilities.

40
00:01:21,810 --> 00:01:24,717
OA records the semantic operation first, then lowers it to an

41
00:01:24,717 --> 00:01:25,510
executable Vulkan graph.

42
00:01:25,510 --> 00:01:27,888
Recorded work and compiled replay amortize host work without

43
00:01:27,888 --> 00:01:30,531
exposing a vendor policy through the high-level API.

44
00:01:30,911 --> 00:01:33,046
The same substrate reaches far beyond the phone.

45
00:01:33,046 --> 00:01:35,180
Audio paths decode, normalize, transform, and extract model-ready

46
00:01:35,180 --> 00:01:35,447
features.

47
00:01:35,447 --> 00:01:37,582
Vision operations preserve image semantics through transforms and

48
00:01:37,582 --> 00:01:37,849
display.

49
00:01:37,849 --> 00:01:39,717
Reinforcement learning connects native environments, models, and

50
00:01:39,717 --> 00:01:39,984
metrics.

51
00:01:39,984 --> 00:01:43,186
The early OaAlm pipeline turns text into skeletal motion

52
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:44,520
and exports USD.

53
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:47,456
Media, plotting, and viewer paths remain in the same system, with

54
00:01:47,456 --> 00:01:49,857
shared values instead of a chain of opaque copies.

55
00:01:50,237 --> 00:01:52,157
At the surface, the intent is deliberately simple.

56
00:01:52,157 --> 00:01:53,117
Load an audio file.

57
00:01:53,117 --> 00:01:53,597
Normalize it.

58
00:01:53,597 --> 00:01:54,557
Compute a mel spectrogram.

59
00:01:54,557 --> 00:01:55,277
Run a model.

60
00:01:55,277 --> 00:01:58,157
The C++ and Python interfaces describe the same work, while

61
00:01:58,157 --> 00:02:00,077
ownership, device choice, and synchronization remain explicit where

62
00:02:00,077 --> 00:02:00,557
they matter.

63
00:02:00,937 --> 00:02:03,837
We built this week with GPT-5.6 in

64
00:02:03,837 --> 00:02:06,254
Codex as an engineering collaborator, not a code vending machine.

65
00:02:06,254 --> 00:02:07,946
Codex audited ownership and synchronization, implemented vertical

66
00:02:07,946 --> 00:02:10,121
changes, constructed differential tests, and repeatedly ran the real

67
00:02:10,121 --> 00:02:10,604
hardware gates.

68
00:02:10,604 --> 00:02:13,021
When the phone exposed corrupt Transformer learning that the desktop

69
00:02:13,021 --> 00:02:15,196
tolerated, the investigation traced it to a thread-varying bindless

70
00:02:15,196 --> 00:02:17,371
descriptor choice in a packed QKV shader.

71
00:02:17,371 --> 00:02:20,029
We corrected the contract, rebuilt the signed app, and reran both

72
00:02:20,029 --> 00:02:20,996
Qualcomm and Intel paths.

73
00:02:20,996 --> 00:02:22,929
The loop was evidence, diagnosis, implementation, and proof.

74
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:25,893
OA 0.7.5 is a development preview, published

75
00:02:25,893 --> 00:02:28,477
by Realm with a signed Android app, Python wheel, Linux packages,

76
00:02:28,477 --> 00:02:28,946
and source.

77
00:02:28,946 --> 00:02:31,295
It targets NVIDIA, AMD, Intel, and Qualcomm through Vulkan, with

78
00:02:31,295 --> 00:02:32,470
verified scope declared per device.

79
00:02:32,470 --> 00:02:35,053
Linux and Android ship now; Windows and macOS compute are planned.

80
00:02:35,053 --> 00:02:36,932
One framework will not make every accelerator identical.

81
00:02:36,932 --> 00:02:38,577
It can make more of them useful.

82
00:02:38,577 --> 00:02:40,925
The accelerator you already own should be able to train.

83
00:02:41,305 --> 00:02:43,297
This was a walkthrough, not the finish line.

84
00:02:43,297 --> 00:02:45,786
The developer pages publish the working base, benchmarks, gaps, and

85
00:02:45,786 --> 00:02:47,777
bounded roadmap: fifty Vision operations, thirteen Audio operation

86
00:02:47,777 --> 00:02:50,267
candidates, five complete mobile training routes, CartPole PPO,

87
00:02:50,267 --> 00:02:51,013
and early text-to-USD.

88
00:02:51,013 --> 00:02:53,503
Explore the architecture, APIs, evidence, and roadmap at dev dot

89
